{"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["# Prepare data (Colab)\n\nThis notebook prepares a *small* dataset subset for validating the Colab workflow.\n\n## Goals\n- confirm `prepare.py` runs successfully\n- start with a small shard count\n- capture logs to a file (helps debugging after runtime resets)\n- verify outputs exist before moving to training\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## 0) Working directory + quick inventory\n\nIf you cloned upstream into a subfolder, you may need to `cd` or update paths below.\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["from pathlib import Path\n\nprint('cwd:', Path('.').resolve())\nprint('Top-level files (first 60):')\nfor p in sorted(Path('.').iterdir())[:60]:\n    print(' -', p.name)\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## 1) Confirm required script exists\n\nThis repo is *Colab companion notes*; it assumes the upstream `prepare.py` is available in your runtime.\n\nIf `prepare.py` is in a subfolder, set `PREPARE_PY` accordingly (example: `upstream/prepare.py`).\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["from pathlib import Path\n\nPREPARE_PY = 'prepare.py'\nprint('prepare.py path:', PREPARE_PY)\nprint('prepare.py exists:', Path(PREPARE_PY).exists())\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## 2) Choose conservative settings\n\nStart small to validate the pipeline first.\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["# Keep this small for first validation\nNUM_SHARDS = 4\n\n# If prepare.py supports a configurable output dir, set it there.\n# Otherwise this is just a note for you to track where files land.\nEXPECTED_OUTPUT_DIR_NOTE = 'data/'\n\nprint('NUM_SHARDS:', NUM_SHARDS)\nprint('Expected output dir note:', EXPECTED_OUTPUT_DIR_NOTE)\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## 3) Run prepare.py (capture logs)\n\nWe capture stdout/stderr to a timestamped file under `logs/`.\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["import time\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nlogs_dir = Path('logs')\nlogs_dir.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\nlog_path = logs_dir / f'prepare_{time.strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S")}.log'\nprint('Log path:', log_path)\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["cmd = f'python {PREPARE_PY} --num-shards {NUM_SHARDS} 2>&1 | tee {log_path}'\nprint('Running:', cmd)\n!bash -lc "$cmd"\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## 4) Sanity check outputs\n\nList candidate output files and show sizes.\nIf this is empty, inspect the log file path printed above.\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["!find . -maxdepth 4 -type f | sort | head -200\n"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":null,"metadata":{},"outputs":[],"source":["# Helpful when outputs are large\n!du -h -d 3 . 2>/dev/null | sort -h | tail -40\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","metadata":{},"source":["## Next step\n\nIf preparation succeeded and outputs exist, continue to `03_train_smoke_test.ipynb`.\n"]}],"metadata":{"colab":{"name":"02_prepare_data.ipynb"},"kernelspec":{"display_name":"Python 3","language":"python","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python"}},"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":5}